12:42.470 --> 12:44.639
‐ Hi.
[both laugh]

12:44.639 --> 12:47.600
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

12:47.600 --> 12:49.018
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:49.018 --> 12:51.229
‐ Come in.

12:51.229 --> 12:53.439
‐ Hello.

12:53.439 --> 12:54.774
I brought these for you, Mari.

12:54.774 --> 12:57.277
‐ Aww, thank you.

12:57.277 --> 12:59.362
‐ And Rafael, I got you a bottle

12:59.362 --> 13:02.740
of 21‐year‐old Monrose rum.

13:02.740 --> 13:03.700
He said it was your favorite.

13:03.700 --> 13:05.493
‐ [laughs]

13:05.493 --> 13:08.246
‐ Very generous.
‐ Thank you.

13:08.246 --> 13:09.872
‐ This is my sister Natalie.

13:09.872 --> 13:11.082
‐ Hi.
‐ Well, hi.

13:11.082 --> 13:12.667
We go way back.
[both laugh]

13:12.667 --> 13:14.377
‐ Yeah, like‐‐
like a whole three weeks.

13:14.377 --> 13:15.920
[laughter]

13:15.920 --> 13:17.422
‐ Just like Daniel.

13:21.634 --> 13:23.136
‐ This is Natalie's friend Amy.

13:23.136 --> 13:24.887
‐ I've been obsessed with you

13:24.887 --> 13:28.683
since you wore that three‐piece
Armani to the Met Gala in 2017.

13:28.683 --> 13:30.101
‐ That's very sweet.
Thank you.

13:34.439 --> 13:36.607
‐ Last but not least,
that's my brother Mateo.

13:36.607 --> 13:38.943
‐ [laughs]

13:38.943 --> 13:40.737
Such a pleasure, Ms. Hamilton,

13:40.737 --> 13:43.072
making your acquaintance
on this fine evening.

13:43.072 --> 13:45.116
Daniel says a lot of nice things
about you.

13:45.116 --> 13:46.492
‐ Likewise.

13:46.492 --> 13:49.078
I really like your song.
We played it at my party.

13:49.078 --> 13:50.913
I think you have a bright future
ahead of you.

13:50.913 --> 13:52.957
‐ That's very kind of you
to say.

13:55.835 --> 13:56.961
‐ Drinks?
‐ Yeah.

13:56.961 --> 13:58.713
‐ Yeah? Yeah.
‐ Yes, come inside.

13:58.713 --> 14:03.176
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:03.176 --> 14:06.012
‐ Look, I'll call you back
in five minutes, okay?

14:06.012 --> 14:07.764
[indistinct chatter]

14:07.764 --> 14:09.348
Trevor, right?

14:09.348 --> 14:10.808
‐ Oh, you must be Lewis.

14:10.808 --> 14:12.727
‐ Let me save us both
a little bit of time.

14:12.727 --> 14:15.688
I'm sure you're a wonderful guy
but this is never gonna work.

14:15.688 --> 14:18.024
‐ Oh, really?
Are you a psychic?

14:18.024 --> 14:20.610
‐ Well, I can tell you
how this is gonna play out.

14:20.610 --> 14:22.320
We'll have fun,
we'll hit it off,

14:22.320 --> 14:23.905
maybe have a roll in the sheets

14:23.905 --> 14:25.490
and even like each other.

14:25.490 --> 14:27.950
At best, we start to date.

14:27.950 --> 14:30.203
Inevitably, I will blow you off
for my work

14:30.203 --> 14:31.412
and you will say
that you don't resent it

14:31.412 --> 14:33.539
but you actually do,
which I will sense

14:33.539 --> 14:35.750
and passive‐aggressively respond
by turning colder

14:35.750 --> 14:38.086
until what started out
as something well‐meaning

14:38.086 --> 14:39.754
leaves us both
feeling a little sad

14:39.754 --> 14:41.089
and like we both wasted
our time.

14:41.089 --> 14:42.965
So nice meeting you.

14:42.965 --> 14:44.509
‐ [laughs]

14:46.803 --> 14:50.014
Noa warned me
you'd say all that.

14:50.014 --> 14:52.975
Let me offer a rewrite
to your story.

14:52.975 --> 14:57.146
The reason that we'll hit it off
is that I'll surprise you.

14:57.146 --> 14:58.314
I'll know that you run
30 minutes late,

14:58.314 --> 15:00.233
so I'll make sure
that our drinks arrive

15:00.233 --> 15:03.111
when you do.

15:03.111 --> 15:04.904
And then I'll draw you
into a great conversation

15:04.904 --> 15:06.447
because even though
I'm a dentist,

15:06.447 --> 15:07.990
I majored in Art History.

15:07.990 --> 15:10.660
And I minored in difficult men

15:10.660 --> 15:12.578
who think
they're emotionally unavailable

15:12.578 --> 15:14.747
but really they're just tired
of being disappointed

15:14.747 --> 15:16.082
by boyfriends who can't see

15:16.082 --> 15:19.627
when they start to build
those invisible walls

15:19.627 --> 15:21.587
around their heart.

15:21.587 --> 15:23.589
‐ Well...

15:23.589 --> 15:24.841
I can't leave now, can I?

15:29.095 --> 15:30.388
‐ It looks like
my first communion,

15:30.388 --> 15:31.806
but it was actually
my first exorcism.

15:31.806 --> 15:34.183
‐ [laughs]
‐ <i>Ay, muchachito.</i>

15:34.183 --> 15:37.311
<i>Mira.</i>
This one is my favorite.

15:37.311 --> 15:40.273
It was impossible
to keep this boy in a diaper.

15:40.273 --> 15:42.233
He used to love
to run around naked,

15:42.233 --> 15:44.986
with his culito hanging out,
right down the street,

15:44.986 --> 15:46.404
booty shaking!

15:46.404 --> 15:47.822
‐ Okay, Mom.
All right, all right, all right.

15:47.822 --> 15:49.824
<i>‐ Mari, por favor, chica.</i>
<i>‐ Ay, por favor.</i>

15:49.824 --> 15:53.077
‐ Rafael, I was hoping
to get a tour of the bakery.

15:53.077 --> 15:56.455
I wanna see where the best
pastries in Miami are made.

15:56.455 --> 15:57.832
‐ You have to finish
the vegetables.
‐ He has to watch the fricasé.

15:57.832 --> 16:00.209
Right?

16:00.209 --> 16:01.544
‐ Sure.

16:01.544 --> 16:08.134
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:15.725 --> 16:17.560
Ta‐da.

16:17.560 --> 16:18.728
‐ [laughs]

16:20.813 --> 16:22.899
So how early
do you have to start?

16:24.734 --> 16:27.570
‐ I'm down here by 5:00 a. m.

16:28.946 --> 16:30.948
Daniel's been
coming down earlier.

16:30.948 --> 16:32.533
Lately.

16:35.453 --> 16:38.164
‐ So where did you learn
to bake?

16:38.164 --> 16:41.918
‐ My‐‐my grandmother
baked at home.

16:41.918 --> 16:43.211
Both of my parents
were always working,

16:43.211 --> 16:45.504
so she looked after me.

16:45.504 --> 16:49.467
She would make me help her
to keep me out of trouble.

16:49.467 --> 16:52.094
So I've tried to do
the same thing for my boys.

16:52.094 --> 16:54.347
Teach them so they can take over
the business one day‐‐

16:54.347 --> 16:57.558
assuming Daniel stays on track.

16:57.558 --> 17:00.102
‐ Mr. Garcia, I can only imagine

17:00.102 --> 17:02.688
how this all must feel.

17:02.688 --> 17:05.524
I know that my life
can get pretty crazy

17:05.524 --> 17:08.778
and I've been a bit of a tornado
coming into your home.

17:11.030 --> 17:14.075
‐ You seem to be a good person.

17:14.075 --> 17:16.619
But your world is...

17:16.619 --> 17:18.871
it's intoxicating.

17:18.871 --> 17:21.165
It's easy to get swept away,

17:21.165 --> 17:23.918
believing that you belong in it

17:23.918 --> 17:26.921
until one day, you wake up
and you realize that you don't.

17:26.921 --> 17:29.340
<i>[heartfelt music]</i>

17:29.340 --> 17:31.384
I don't want Daniel
to lose sight of who he is

17:31.384 --> 17:33.135
and where he's going

17:33.135 --> 17:37.390
in exchange for
a few weeks or months

17:37.390 --> 17:41.060
of living someone else's life.

17:41.060 --> 17:43.271
‐ I care about your son.

17:43.271 --> 17:45.773
And I share your concerns.

17:45.773 --> 17:48.818
Daniel is a good man

17:48.818 --> 17:51.362
from a good family.

17:51.362 --> 17:54.699
That's why I like him.

17:54.699 --> 17:56.200
‐ I appreciate that.

17:56.200 --> 18:00.621
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:00.621 --> 18:03.541
We should go back upstairs.
Dinner should be ready.

18:03.541 --> 18:04.834
And Mari will kill me

18:04.834 --> 18:06.460
if I don't serve you
the best meal you've ever had.

18:06.460 --> 18:07.628
‐ [laughs]

18:07.628 --> 18:10.214
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:10.214 --> 18:11.632
Mmm.

18:11.632 --> 18:13.217
It smells delicious.

18:13.217 --> 18:15.469
‐ Mm, thank you.

18:15.469 --> 18:19.265
That's because my husband
is an incredible chef.

18:19.265 --> 18:20.891
[both laugh]
‐ Mwah.

18:20.891 --> 18:22.393
‐ Did you ever think of opening
a restaurant?

18:22.393 --> 18:24.353
‐ Ah, funny you should ask that

18:24.353 --> 18:26.689
because the place next door
is going out of business

18:26.689 --> 18:30.109
and I've been saying
it would be a great café.

18:31.736 --> 18:34.155
That was our plan, you know,
before we left Cuba.

18:34.155 --> 18:37.533
‐ Expansion is
a young man's dream.

18:37.533 --> 18:38.909
Maybe when Daniel takes over.

18:38.909 --> 18:41.245
Right, son?

18:41.245 --> 18:43.414
‐ 'Sup?
Oh.

18:43.414 --> 18:45.458
It smells tight in here.

18:45.458 --> 18:47.043
I hope you don't mind
the quick change.

18:47.043 --> 18:50.004
I had a little stain
on my shirt.

18:50.004 --> 18:51.005
You want me to sing Grace?

18:51.005 --> 18:52.256
both: No.

18:52.256 --> 18:53.299
‐ Let's do this.

18:53.299 --> 18:56.344
<i>[upbeat trumpet music]</i>

18:56.344 --> 19:03.184
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:04.602 --> 19:07.647
<i>[woman singing in Spanish]</i>

19:07.647 --> 19:09.023
‐ [laughs]

19:09.023 --> 19:16.072
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:38.552 --> 19:39.887
‐ Wyoming?

19:39.887 --> 19:41.097
[laughs]
‐ Mm‐hmm.

19:41.097 --> 19:43.766
Rock Springs, born and raised.

19:43.766 --> 19:45.685
What?
It's not obvious?

19:45.685 --> 19:47.895
‐ Last time you were back?

19:47.895 --> 19:49.772
‐ Dad's funeral eight years ago.

19:49.772 --> 19:52.108
It was the first time
since I was 20.

19:52.108 --> 19:54.402
‐ How was that?

19:54.402 --> 19:57.029
‐ Well, it's like they say.

19:57.029 --> 20:00.408
Growing up, it all seems so big.

20:00.408 --> 20:04.036
Going back,
it all seems so small.

20:04.036 --> 20:06.372
My family thinks I'm an alien.

20:06.372 --> 20:09.083
Ex‐model turned manager?
Strike one and two.

20:10.918 --> 20:12.420
And there's the tiny fact
that I left my wife.

20:14.672 --> 20:16.382
What?

20:16.382 --> 20:20.136
‐ Did you ever, like,
really think you were straight?

20:20.136 --> 20:21.470
‐ I hoped.

20:21.470 --> 20:23.305
I know that's a terrible thing
to say now,

20:23.305 --> 20:26.892
but when you're 18
and living at home?

20:26.892 --> 20:28.144
‐ I wanna see wedding pics.

20:28.144 --> 20:29.478
‐ Oh.
‐ [laughs]

20:29.478 --> 20:31.021
‐ You just wanna get a look
at my ex‐wife.

20:31.021 --> 20:32.565
‐ [laughs]
‐ Don't kid yourself.

20:32.565 --> 20:34.817
She was hot.
She just had no sense of style.

20:34.817 --> 20:36.402
‐ Ah.
‐ Oof, the zippers.

20:36.402 --> 20:39.822
‐ [laughs]

20:39.822 --> 20:41.073
‐ You know,
I didn't wanna come tonight.

20:41.073 --> 20:43.159
‐ Mm.

20:43.159 --> 20:44.910
You hid that so well.
[laughs]

20:44.910 --> 20:46.787
‐ But I'm actually happy
that Noa's off with Baker Boy

20:46.787 --> 20:48.539
in Little Havana.

20:48.539 --> 20:51.167
<i>[tense music]</i>

20:51.167 --> 20:53.461
Because this...

20:53.461 --> 20:55.838
is nice.

20:55.838 --> 21:02.928
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:07.475 --> 21:09.435
‐ And what about you, Mari?
How did you meet Rafael?

21:09.435 --> 21:11.270
‐ Yeah, Ma, tell her.
It's such a good story.

21:11.270 --> 21:13.105
They were 19.
Just kids.

21:13.105 --> 21:15.566
‐ Yeah.
Yeah.

21:15.566 --> 21:19.904
Well, we were both working
at the Tropicana in Havana.

21:19.904 --> 21:21.822
He was a pastry chef.
‐ Mm‐hmm.

21:21.822 --> 21:24.492
‐ And I had just started out
as a dancer.

21:24.492 --> 21:28.287
‐ It's hard to stand out
among a bunch of showgirls,

21:28.287 --> 21:31.624
but Mari was like
a ray of sunshine.

21:31.624 --> 21:33.542
‐ Aww.

21:33.542 --> 21:35.836
‐ Hey, you should check out
the pictures that she's in.

21:35.836 --> 21:38.589
In that whole outfit
with the headdress

21:38.589 --> 21:40.216
and that little bikini!

21:40.216 --> 21:41.675
[laughter and cheering]
‐ Okay.

21:41.675 --> 21:43.219
It was like a big, tall bird.
‐ Mama was banging.

21:43.219 --> 21:44.386
‐ Yeah.
‐ Aw, Mateo.

21:44.386 --> 21:45.805
Please don't call our mother
banging.

21:45.805 --> 21:47.515
[laughter]
‐ I see. Okay.

21:47.515 --> 21:48.933
‐ Stop!
‐ Anyways.

21:48.933 --> 21:52.520
So one night,
the featured girl got sick

21:52.520 --> 21:54.897
and I was the only one
who knew the song

21:54.897 --> 21:58.234
and I knew this was
going to be my shot.

21:58.234 --> 22:01.362
But I was so nervous
and I couldn't breathe.

22:01.362 --> 22:02.655
‐ [laughs]

22:02.655 --> 22:04.907
So I was trying to find
an excuse to talk to her.

22:04.907 --> 22:06.951
So when I found out
what was happening,

22:06.951 --> 22:08.786
I brought her a buchito de ron.

22:08.786 --> 22:10.120
‐ [laughs]
Yes.

22:10.120 --> 22:13.165
‐ And I said, "Don't be scared

22:13.165 --> 22:15.751
of having your dreams
come true because"‐‐

22:15.751 --> 22:20.130
‐ "Because it makes room
for bigger and better ones."

22:20.130 --> 22:22.299
‐ That's right.

22:27.179 --> 22:29.139
‐ Anyway, finally,
they made me the featured girl!

22:29.139 --> 22:31.058
[laughter and cheering]

22:31.058 --> 22:31.934
‐ Cheers.
‐ <i>Salud, salud.</i>

22:31.934 --> 22:34.061
Drink to that.
‐ Yes.

22:34.061 --> 22:36.480
<i>Salud, salud.</i>
[laughs]

22:36.480 --> 22:38.691
Yeah.

22:38.691 --> 22:41.110
‐ [laughs]

22:41.110 --> 22:44.446
And so what about
you two lovebirds?

22:44.446 --> 22:45.656
How did you guys meet?

22:52.580 --> 22:54.665
‐ Oh, they're not a couple.
They're just friends.

22:54.665 --> 22:57.418
‐ Yeah.
[laughter]

22:57.418 --> 22:59.420
‐ Right, mami?

23:04.800 --> 23:06.260
Natalie.

23:06.260 --> 23:08.345
‐ Natalie,
please answer your mother.

23:08.345 --> 23:09.930
‐ We're just friends.

23:19.481 --> 23:20.900
[door closes]

23:20.900 --> 23:23.402
Uh, I'm just‐‐I'm just gonna...

23:31.619 --> 23:37.458
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:37.458 --> 23:40.586
‐ What the hell
is going on here?

23:40.586 --> 23:41.670
‐ Vanessa.

23:41.670 --> 23:46.008
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:46.008 --> 23:47.092
‐ [hoarsely]
Vanessa.

23:50.638 --> 23:52.139
‐ Family dinner?

23:52.139 --> 23:54.099
You invited her
to family dinner?

23:54.099 --> 23:55.768
‐ V, what are you doing here?

23:55.768 --> 23:59.772
‐ I brought soup for Mateo
for his sore throat.

23:59.772 --> 24:02.733
What is she doing here?

24:02.733 --> 24:05.110
It took me six months
to be invited to one of these.

24:05.110 --> 24:06.445
It was three months, Mari,

24:06.445 --> 24:10.157
until you even
smiled at me, and...

24:10.157 --> 24:13.452
in four years, you never once
made me fricasé de pollo, Rafi.

24:16.455 --> 24:17.915
I just don't understand

24:17.915 --> 24:19.750
why you all would treat her
better than me.

24:19.750 --> 24:21.877
‐ Vanessa, stop.

24:21.877 --> 24:23.212
Look‐‐

24:23.212 --> 24:24.755
‐ Don't touch me.

24:28.008 --> 24:30.594
‐ Let's go talk.

24:30.594 --> 24:31.887
Okay?

24:34.098 --> 24:37.142
<i>[tense percussive music]</i>

24:37.142 --> 24:39.436
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:39.436 --> 24:42.314
‐ Oh!

24:42.314 --> 24:44.900
‐ Find yourself a new manager.

24:47.277 --> 24:49.196
‐ What is it with this girl
and soup?

24:49.196 --> 24:50.781
<i>[heartfelt music]</i>

24:50.781 --> 24:53.534
‐ [scoffs]
Daniel.

24:53.534 --> 24:54.868
I have been patient.

24:54.868 --> 24:56.495
I have been understanding.

24:56.495 --> 24:57.913
You were having a moment

24:57.913 --> 24:59.832
and I've been giving you
the space to move through it.

24:59.832 --> 25:02.459
‐ I didn't ask for space.
‐ You don't have to.

25:02.459 --> 25:05.004
That's just what you do.

25:05.004 --> 25:06.380
That's what people
who love each other,

25:06.380 --> 25:08.924
people who have been together
for four years, do.

25:08.924 --> 25:11.552
They don't just bail
when they hit a road bump.

25:11.552 --> 25:13.512
They don't just erase
the other person

25:13.512 --> 25:15.597
and act like they don't exist.

25:15.597 --> 25:19.268
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:19.268 --> 25:22.312
‐ What just happened?

25:22.312 --> 25:25.399
Did I just come out?

25:25.399 --> 25:27.192
Did I just tell my very,

25:27.192 --> 25:30.404
very Catholic parents that I'm‐‐

25:30.404 --> 25:33.824
‐ I don't think so.

25:33.824 --> 25:37.036
With what Noa said
and the way that you left,

25:37.036 --> 25:39.413
my guess is your parents
are probably just as confused

25:39.413 --> 25:40.706
as you are right now.

25:40.706 --> 25:44.710
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:58.891 --> 26:00.309
‐ ♪ 'Cause I'm
a Calle Ocho guy ♪

26:00.309 --> 26:03.103
‐ Mateo, go change your clothes.
‐ Yep.

26:03.103 --> 26:04.813
‐ I don't know
what you want me to say.

26:04.813 --> 26:08.650
‐ I want to finish
the conversation we started

26:08.650 --> 26:10.402
the night after I proposed.

26:15.407 --> 26:19.286
We have put so much
into building something real,

26:19.286 --> 26:22.748
something that matters.

26:22.748 --> 26:25.501
Are you really gonna
throw it all away

26:25.501 --> 26:29.254
on a fantasy?

26:29.254 --> 26:31.298
‐ I'm not going
to pressure you, Nat.

26:31.298 --> 26:34.051
It's really hard
coming out to anyone,

26:34.051 --> 26:35.594
let alone your parents.

26:35.594 --> 26:37.930
‐ So you're not mad that I ran?

26:37.930 --> 26:39.765
‐ No.

26:39.765 --> 26:42.810
Whatever makes you happy.

26:42.810 --> 26:45.938
Whatever you want...

26:45.938 --> 26:47.439
I want.

26:47.439 --> 26:51.068
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:51.068 --> 26:52.444
‐ I want this.

26:52.444 --> 26:59.243
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:05.541 --> 27:08.252
‐ I feel like this is my fault.

27:08.252 --> 27:09.628
I shouldn't have jumped
to a silly conclusion‐‐

27:09.628 --> 27:11.713
‐ Sorry, but I prefer
that you mind your own business.

27:11.713 --> 27:13.590
This is a family matter.

27:13.590 --> 27:17.970
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:17.970 --> 27:20.264
‐ My apologies,
but I think dinner's over.

27:20.264 --> 27:25.894
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:25.894 --> 27:27.896
‐ [indistinct whispering]

27:27.896 --> 27:29.398
And it's gonna be okay.

27:29.398 --> 27:36.196
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:43.078 --> 27:44.705
[paparazzi shouting outside]

27:44.705 --> 27:47.833
<i>[tense Latin music]</i>

27:47.833 --> 27:54.840
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:57.843 --> 28:00.012
[phone ringing]
‐ Oh, sorry.

28:00.012 --> 28:01.930
Bat phone.

28:01.930 --> 28:05.434
Hey.

28:05.434 --> 28:07.269
What?

28:07.269 --> 28:09.313
Okay, don't do anything.

28:09.313 --> 28:10.772
I'm on my way.

28:10.772 --> 28:13.817
‐ Vanessa, I do love you.

28:15.569 --> 28:18.363
But not like I used to.

28:18.363 --> 28:20.115
I think I felt this way
for a while

28:20.115 --> 28:21.867
but didn't realize it
until you proposed.

28:21.867 --> 28:24.995
It's not about Noa
or some fantasy.

28:24.995 --> 28:29.249
You and I are not gonna be

28:29.249 --> 28:32.461
"happily ever after."

28:32.461 --> 28:34.630
Okay?

28:34.630 --> 28:36.006
‐ Okay.

28:38.634 --> 28:39.635
[both grunt]

28:39.635 --> 28:43.221
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:43.221 --> 28:46.391
I'm leaving.

28:46.391 --> 28:49.353
‐ I'm trapped.

28:49.353 --> 28:52.147
‐ I'm gay.

28:52.147 --> 28:54.524
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:59.237 --> 29:00.781
‐ First of all, you don't know
what you're talking about!

29:00.781 --> 29:02.699
‐ Yes, I do.
‐ No, you don't!

29:02.699 --> 29:05.077
‐ You're too young to know
anything about being gay,
Natalie!

29:05.077 --> 29:06.328
‐ Too young?
‐ Yes!

29:06.328 --> 29:08.580
‐ I'm almost 16!
‐ Exactly!

29:08.580 --> 29:10.582
You're not even old enough
to drive yet, let alone make‐‐

29:10.582 --> 29:12.834
‐ Let's all calm down, Mari.
‐ These kinds of decisions
about your life.

29:12.834 --> 29:14.419
‐ Decisions?
‐ Yes!

29:14.419 --> 29:15.837
‐ You know what, you're the one

29:15.837 --> 29:17.381
who has no idea
what you're talking about.

29:17.381 --> 29:19.424
This isn't like
choosing some dress

29:19.424 --> 29:22.511
for that stupid quinceañera
you keep wanting to throw me.

29:22.511 --> 29:24.096
‐ Don't you change the subject
on me!

29:24.096 --> 29:26.014
‐ Actually, you know what?
Maybe it is just like that.

29:26.014 --> 29:28.558
I don't have a choice
in throwing that party

29:28.558 --> 29:30.894
just like I don't have a choice
in who I am.

29:32.646 --> 29:35.816
This is who I am.

29:35.816 --> 29:37.317
So you?

29:37.317 --> 29:39.277
You'll just have to deal
with it.

29:39.277 --> 29:42.948
‐ Natalie Garcia,
do not take that tone of voice
with your mother!

29:42.948 --> 29:44.658
‐ Come on, Amy.
I'm done here.

29:47.744 --> 29:50.205
‐ Mari.
‐ [sobbing]

29:50.205 --> 29:51.456
‐ Mari.

29:51.456 --> 29:53.041
Mari.

30:07.681 --> 30:09.349
‐ You know what
I don't understand

30:09.349 --> 30:12.310
is why you feel trapped.

30:12.310 --> 30:16.440
I was always proud to be seen
with Daniel and his family.

30:16.440 --> 30:17.691
If I were you,
I'd go out there right now

30:17.691 --> 30:19.317
and tell anyone who listened
how happy I was

30:19.317 --> 30:20.944
to be sitting in that chair
tonight.

30:20.944 --> 30:23.238
‐ It's not like that.
‐ It's not?

30:23.238 --> 30:24.906
Oh, so you're saying
you'd be fine

30:24.906 --> 30:28.660
if I went out there right now
and told everyone you were here?

30:28.660 --> 30:31.663
<i>[tense music]</i>

30:31.663 --> 30:35.667
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:35.667 --> 30:38.920
‐ Yo, Vanessa, wait!
Wait.

30:38.920 --> 30:40.505
‐ I gotta tell Lewis.

30:40.505 --> 30:41.715
‐ Yeah.

30:41.715 --> 30:47.679
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:47.679 --> 30:48.638
‐ I don't think
this is a good idea.

30:48.638 --> 30:49.890
‐ Really?
‐ Yeah.

30:49.890 --> 30:51.433
‐ "Noa Hamilton: Home‐wrecker."

30:51.433 --> 30:53.060
Sounds like a great headline
to me.

30:53.060 --> 30:55.520
‐ Listen, you're not thinking
this through, all right?

30:55.520 --> 30:56.938
What good can come out of it?
It's not gonna change anything.

30:56.938 --> 30:58.231
‐ Mateo?
‐ Yeah?

30:58.231 --> 31:00.442
‐ Move.

31:00.442 --> 31:02.319
‐ Vanessa,
you are better than this.

31:02.319 --> 31:05.322
‐ [scoffs]
‐ You know I'm right.

31:05.322 --> 31:08.158
You know that there's someone
out there waiting for you.

31:08.158 --> 31:10.160
Waiting to see what
an incredible woman you are.

31:10.160 --> 31:13.038
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:13.038 --> 31:17.167
A man who loves your strength,

31:17.167 --> 31:19.169
your intelligence,

31:19.169 --> 31:22.672
your beauty.

31:22.672 --> 31:27.385
Someone who'll treat you
like the amazing person you are.

31:27.385 --> 31:29.596
‐ Mateo?
‐ Yeah?

31:29.596 --> 31:31.640
‐ Move before
I rip your face off.

31:31.640 --> 31:33.725
‐ Yeah.

31:33.725 --> 31:35.894
[paparazzi shouting]

31:35.894 --> 31:37.729
‐ Somebody's coming out
right now.

31:37.729 --> 31:39.022
‐ She's coming out!

31:39.022 --> 31:41.233
‐ Oh, my God.

31:41.233 --> 31:42.651
‐ Who are you?
What's your name?

31:42.651 --> 31:43.985
‐ Is Noa Hamilton inside?

31:43.985 --> 31:45.153
‐ Did you have dinner with her?

31:45.153 --> 31:46.196
‐ Who are you?
‐ Hey, who are you?

31:46.196 --> 31:47.948
‐ Is Noa in there?

31:47.948 --> 31:50.575
[paparazzi shouting]

31:50.575 --> 31:52.119
‐ What's your name?

31:52.119 --> 31:54.663
‐ Is Noa still in there?

31:54.663 --> 31:56.206
‐ Excuse me, are you friends
with Ms. Hamilton?

31:56.206 --> 31:58.542
‐ Where is Noa?
Where is Noa?

31:58.542 --> 32:00.794
Excuse me!
What is your name?

32:00.794 --> 32:02.462
Miss!

32:02.462 --> 32:08.176
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:08.176 --> 32:09.761
‐ Oh, no.
They've got the place blanketed.

32:09.761 --> 32:11.138
There's, like,
a dozen in the front

32:11.138 --> 32:12.764
and at least two
going in the back.

32:12.764 --> 32:15.183
‐ I'm sorry, Lewis.

32:15.183 --> 32:16.726
You warned me.

32:16.726 --> 32:19.604
‐ Don't worry.
I will get you out of this.

32:19.604 --> 32:21.773
<i>Okay?</i>

32:21.773 --> 32:25.652
I just have no idea how.

32:25.652 --> 32:27.445
[sighs]

32:27.445 --> 32:30.073
‐ I don't understand.
Why wouldn't she tell us?

32:31.658 --> 32:33.702
‐ She's 15, Mari.

32:33.702 --> 32:35.412
There's a hundred reasons why.

32:35.412 --> 32:37.330
It's not anything
to take personally.

32:37.330 --> 32:39.040
‐ Well, maybe you don't
take personally

32:39.040 --> 32:41.626
that your only daughter would
keep a secret like this

32:41.626 --> 32:43.503
from you but I do!

32:43.503 --> 32:45.589
‐ Mari‐‐
‐ I should've seen this.

32:48.758 --> 32:49.968
I...

32:53.013 --> 32:56.391
[sobbing]
She's my baby girl.

32:56.391 --> 32:59.436
When did I stop knowing
who my daughter was?

33:02.731 --> 33:05.317
‐ I think she's coming out!
‐ She's coming out!

33:05.317 --> 33:07.569
‐ Oh, no.
That's not her.

33:07.569 --> 33:09.946
‐ That's not her.
‐ No, that's not her?

33:09.946 --> 33:13.909
‐ That's twice in one night.

33:13.909 --> 33:15.285
‐ Maybe you should
go down there.

33:15.285 --> 33:17.537
Let them see you.
Would it really be that bad?

33:17.537 --> 33:21.124
‐ It's not me I'm worried about.
It's you and your family.

33:21.124 --> 33:22.542
If I go out there now,

33:22.542 --> 33:25.045
then everyone goes under
the microscope.

33:25.045 --> 33:26.463
And it is so much worse

33:26.463 --> 33:28.506
than if you and I come out
as a couple in some other way.

33:28.506 --> 33:30.091
‐ Why?

33:30.091 --> 33:32.093
‐ Because if they take
my picture in front of here,

33:32.093 --> 33:34.554
then suddenly this dinner
becomes part of the story

33:34.554 --> 33:36.640
and they're gonna wanna know
who was here.

33:36.640 --> 33:40.310
Mateo, Natalie, Vanessa.

33:40.310 --> 33:44.314
You don't know how invasive
these tabloids can be.

33:44.314 --> 33:46.316
If anyone decides
to be in the spotlight,

33:46.316 --> 33:48.985
that should be their choice.

33:48.985 --> 33:51.112
I shouldn't have come here.
I'm sorry.

33:52.989 --> 33:55.408
I just really wanted to meet
your family.

33:57.744 --> 33:59.788
‐ Come with me.

33:59.788 --> 34:01.873
There's a third way out of here.

34:01.873 --> 34:05.293
<i>[low exciting music]</i>

34:05.293 --> 34:07.504
‐ Noa, I'm still working on it,
okay?

34:07.504 --> 34:10.173
I‐‐what?

34:10.173 --> 34:11.591
A tunnel?

34:11.591 --> 34:13.218
‐ Back in Prohibition days,

34:13.218 --> 34:15.345
this bakery was also used
as a warehouse

34:15.345 --> 34:17.222
to store liquor that came in
from Jamaica.

34:17.222 --> 34:19.224
‐ Pop, why didn't you ever
tell us about this?

34:19.224 --> 34:20.392
‐ Why didn't I ever tell
my children

34:20.392 --> 34:22.060
how to sneak out
of their own home?

34:22.060 --> 34:24.479
<i>Por favor.</i>

34:24.479 --> 34:29.025
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:29.025 --> 34:30.819
‐ Okay, then.

34:30.819 --> 34:32.362
‐ Be careful, eh?

34:32.362 --> 34:39.119
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:40.996 --> 34:42.789
‐ You okay?
‐ Yeah.

34:42.789 --> 34:48.461
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:48.461 --> 34:50.839
‐ Carve a path, guys.
Carve a path.

34:50.839 --> 34:52.507
‐ Are you coming to pick her up?
Hey.

34:52.507 --> 34:54.509
‐ She's coming out now!

34:54.509 --> 34:55.677
[all shouting excitedly]

34:55.677 --> 35:00.640
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:00.640 --> 35:01.891
‐ What is going‐‐

35:01.891 --> 35:02.809
[mouse squeaks]
‐ [yelps]

35:02.809 --> 35:04.227
‐ You all right?
You okay?

35:04.227 --> 35:05.979
[all shouting excitedly]

35:05.979 --> 35:07.439
‐ Lewis?
‐ It's not her.

35:07.439 --> 35:09.691
‐ It's not her, it's not her.
‐ Your pastries.

35:09.691 --> 35:11.568
‐ Really appreciate it,
Mr. Garcia.

35:11.568 --> 35:14.946
Noa's got friends over and these
are the best pastries in Miami.

35:14.946 --> 35:17.282
‐ Send her my regards.
I'm happy that she's a customer.

35:17.282 --> 35:18.533
‐ I will.

35:18.533 --> 35:22.871
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:22.871 --> 35:25.332
Good night, guys, ladies.

35:25.332 --> 35:27.542
[disappointed chatter]

35:27.542 --> 35:29.586
‐ There's the door.

35:29.586 --> 35:32.255
Okay.

35:32.255 --> 35:33.590
Okay.
‐ Hey.

35:33.590 --> 35:35.216
I'm sorry about tonight.

35:35.216 --> 35:38.094
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:38.094 --> 35:39.638
‐ You ready?
‐ Yeah.

35:39.638 --> 35:45.185
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:45.185 --> 35:48.188
‐ Noa, introduce us
to your friend.

35:57.739 --> 35:59.157
[knocking on door]

35:59.157 --> 36:00.825
<i>‐ I'm coming in.</i>

36:08.833 --> 36:12.337
What a night, huh?

36:12.337 --> 36:13.880
‐ Dad, we don't have to talk
about this now.

36:13.880 --> 36:15.882
‐ Just listen for a moment.

36:19.552 --> 36:21.888
I don't know for sure,

36:21.888 --> 36:24.766
but you've probably been living
with this secret for some time.

36:26.893 --> 36:29.688
‐ Yes.

36:29.688 --> 36:32.357
‐ And we've known for...

36:32.357 --> 36:34.109
12 hours, give or take?

36:34.109 --> 36:36.778
‐ I wanted to tell you guys.

36:36.778 --> 36:40.240
I‐‐I just didn't know how.

36:40.240 --> 36:42.992
‐ Well, that problem's solved.

36:42.992 --> 36:45.120
‐ [laughs]

36:47.455 --> 36:50.542
‐ Everything your mother and I
do in this life

36:50.542 --> 36:52.419
is for you and your brothers.

36:52.419 --> 36:56.673
There is nothing
that you can do or be

36:56.673 --> 36:58.675
that will make us love you
any less.

36:58.675 --> 37:01.219
<i>[heartfelt music]</i>

37:01.219 --> 37:05.056
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:05.056 --> 37:09.102
Give your mom some time.
Okay?

37:09.102 --> 37:12.772
She's an amazing woman.

37:12.772 --> 37:17.610
But 12 hours versus 15 years
of her imagining your life...

37:17.610 --> 37:21.239
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:21.239 --> 37:24.451
Just give her
a little more time.

37:24.451 --> 37:26.661
Okay?

37:26.661 --> 37:29.247
I love you.

37:29.247 --> 37:30.749
‐ I love you too.

37:30.749 --> 37:37.714
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:41.342 --> 37:42.719
<i>‐ Hi, you've reached Trevor.</i>

37:42.719 --> 37:44.220
<i>Please leave a message</i>
<i>and I'll get back to you</i>

37:44.220 --> 37:46.181
<i>as soon as I can.</i>

37:46.181 --> 37:48.183
‐ Hey.
It's Lewis.

37:48.183 --> 37:50.185
Just wanted to thank you again
for last night.

37:50.185 --> 37:52.937
And sorry about all the drama.
[laughs]

37:52.937 --> 37:55.315
Anyway,

37:55.315 --> 37:57.066
despite being
a really good date,

37:57.066 --> 38:01.446
I just think it's better
if we don't see each other.

38:01.446 --> 38:04.324
I know you're gonna come up
with some very clever comeback,

38:04.324 --> 38:08.578
but do me a favor and...
don't use it.

38:08.578 --> 38:10.121
[laughs]

38:10.121 --> 38:11.915
I know what I'm talking about.

38:13.875 --> 38:15.668
Okay, bye.

38:15.668 --> 38:17.754
<i>[keypad beeps]</i>

38:19.380 --> 38:21.007
‐ Okay, Lewis.

38:21.007 --> 38:24.010
I compared today's ultrasound
with the one from six months ago

38:24.010 --> 38:28.097
and I'm afraid the time
of "wait and see" is over.

38:28.097 --> 38:30.642
So let's talk
about your options.

38:30.642 --> 38:34.813
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:34.813 --> 38:36.147
<i>‐ I don't wanna leave.</i>

38:36.147 --> 38:37.774
<i>‐ That guy got us both</i>
<i>on camera.</i>

38:37.774 --> 38:38.942
You know we have to face
the music.

38:38.942 --> 38:40.610
‐ No, not yet.

38:40.610 --> 38:42.737
‐ We can't live in here forever.
‐ Well, not forever,

38:42.737 --> 38:45.615
but if I had Lewis
bring us food and water,

38:45.615 --> 38:47.325
we could last at least a month.

38:47.325 --> 38:49.410
‐ Yeah, I'm sure he would love
to be my personal butler.

38:49.410 --> 38:51.913
‐ Oh, my God.
He would love that.

38:53.331 --> 38:55.542
Daniel...

38:55.542 --> 38:58.753
you know your dad has a point.

38:58.753 --> 39:01.464
I have dated normal guys before.

39:01.464 --> 39:02.966
Twice.

39:02.966 --> 39:06.344
And both times were not great.

39:06.344 --> 39:09.597
The first guy,
he changed when we went public,

39:09.597 --> 39:12.058
and the second guy
just couldn't handle it.

39:12.058 --> 39:13.601
‐ Third time's the charm, right?

39:19.566 --> 39:21.150
‐ [squeals]

39:21.150 --> 39:24.404
‐ Every relationship
is all or nothing.

39:24.404 --> 39:26.030
It always ends up
one of two ways‐‐

39:26.030 --> 39:29.951
either happily ever after
or up in flames.

39:29.951 --> 39:31.494
I mean,

39:31.494 --> 39:34.080
Vanessa's not all that happy
with me right now.

39:34.080 --> 39:37.542
‐ But Daniel, no relationship
you have ever been in

39:37.542 --> 39:40.837
can prepare you
for what this life is like.

39:40.837 --> 39:43.798
I just wanna make sure you know
what you're signing up for.

39:43.798 --> 39:47.260
‐ Well, we can't
undo last night,

39:47.260 --> 39:50.597
so it's either
we take this leap of faith

39:50.597 --> 39:53.182
or we break up.

39:53.182 --> 39:55.935
‐ I know that sounds crazy,
but yes.

39:57.770 --> 39:59.480
‐ I think I could do
a little crazy.

39:59.480 --> 40:01.816
‐ Okay.

40:01.816 --> 40:05.570
If you think you can
handle it...

40:05.570 --> 40:08.448
let's see what it's like
outside the bubble.

40:08.448 --> 40:09.991
Ready?

40:09.991 --> 40:11.576
‐ Yeah.

40:11.576 --> 40:14.454
both: One, two, three.

40:14.454 --> 40:15.955
<i>‐ ♪ Low‐key, low‐key ♪</i>

40:15.955 --> 40:18.041
<i>♪ You should really</i>
<i>get to know me ♪</i>

40:18.041 --> 40:20.668
<i>♪ Really get to know me ♪</i>

40:20.668 --> 40:23.046
‐ Whoa, there's, like,
a hundred messages on here.

40:23.046 --> 40:25.089
‐ That's 'cause
you're famous now.

40:27.175 --> 40:29.510
"The Baker and the Beauty."

40:31.054 --> 40:32.847
‐ It's got a nice ring to it.

40:32.847 --> 40:36.559
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:38.978 --> 40:42.023
<i>[upbeat Latin music]</i>

40:42.023 --> 40:47.028
<i>♪ ♪</i>
